citeinfo.title: Vegetation_CN
citeinfo.othercit: The data for this map was provided by various sources and mapping scales vary from 1:1,200 to 1:24,000. The boundaries are applicable for the San Diego region with the exclusion of the City of Carlsbad, Anza-Borrego State Park and some BLM, Indian Reservations and private lands in the east county. The map projection and coordinate system is the California State Plane Coordinate System, Zone 6, North American Datum 83 (NAD83), units in feet.

descript.abstract: Vegetation Information in the San Diego Region. Maintained by San Diego County Department of Planning and Landuse and updated using aerial imagery and georeferenced bio-maps.
descript.purpose: To illustrate the vegetation communities and disturbed areas throughout San Diego County

idinfo.useconst: Modifications, corrections or updates can be made on request. DPLU-GIS would be happy to consider external information sources as input to future versions of the vegetation layer.

attr.attrdef: Description of Terrestrial Vegetation Communities in San Diego County (See Overview Description)
Code representing Terrestrial Vegetation Communities in San Diego County (See Overview Description)

This indicates what a vegetation type was prior to disturbance. This is what this polygon contained in 1995 and has since been updated as a result of permanent disturbance (such as development). If the polygon is blank, the polygon has either not been disturbed or has not been recently updated. The edit data and disturbance source should indicate the presence and type of disturbance.
